# Operations Documentation Guide

> How to create and update deployment and operations documentation

## When to Create

- When project has deployment requirements
- Before production deployment
- When infrastructure changes

## Profile-Specific Guidance

### Tauri (Local Desktop App)
**Create ops docs?** ❌ No
- Local applications don't need deployment documentation
- Focus on build/distribution instead (covered in SETUP.md)

### Next.js-AWS / Tauri-AWS (Cloud Components)
**Create ops docs?** ✅ Yes
- Document cloud infrastructure
- Deployment procedures
- Monitoring and maintenance

## Core Document: DEPLOYMENT.md

### Purpose
- Guide production deployment
- Document infrastructure
- Provide runbook for operations

### Structure

```markdown
## Infrastructure Overview
- Cloud provider (AWS, GCP, Azure, Vercel, etc.)
- Services used (EC2, Lambda, S3, etc.)
- Architecture diagram

## Deployment Process

### Prerequisites
- AWS CLI configured
- Access credentials
- Domain configured

### Deployment Steps

\```bash
# Build production artifacts
npm run build

# Deploy to production
npm run deploy

# Verify deployment
npm run verify
\```

### Rollback Procedure
1. {ROLLBACK_STEP_1}
2. {ROLLBACK_STEP_2}

## Environment Variables
| Variable | Purpose | Required |
|----------|---------|----------|
| API_KEY | {DESCRIPTION} | Yes |
| DATABASE_URL | {DESCRIPTION} | Yes |

## Monitoring
- Health check endpoint: /api/health
- Logs location: {WHERE}
- Alerts configured: {WHAT}

## Troubleshooting
### Issue 1: {COMMON_PROBLEM}
**Symptoms**: {DESCRIPTION}
**Solution**: {FIX_STEPS}
```

## Quality Standards

- ✅ **Step-by-step deployment** instructions
- ✅ **Rollback procedure** documented
- ✅ **Environment variables** listed
- ✅ **Monitoring setup** described
- ✅ **Common issues** with solutions

## Optional Sections

### For Complex Infrastructure
- **Scaling**: How to scale up/down
- **Backup/Restore**: Data backup procedures
- **Security**: Security best practices
- **Cost Optimization**: Cost management tips

### For CI/CD Pipelines
- **Pipeline Configuration**: GitHub Actions, CircleCI, etc.
- **Automated Tests**: Pre-deployment checks
- **Deployment Stages**: Staging, production

## Template Location

Use template: `framework/guides/ops/templates/DEPLOYMENT.md.template`

